<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[192,1440,770,826]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,770,794]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The greatly enlarged hind femora, in combination with the regularly vittate elytra, immediately distinguish this species from all other chrysomelids known to occur in the 
<collectingCountry box="[1164,1365,802,826]" name="Cayman Islands" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Cayman Islands</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="23.[192,1441,866,954]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,453,866,890]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Material examined.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation collectingDate="1993-11-20" collectionCode="BYUC, USNM" collectorName="F. J. Burton" country="Cayman Islands" location="Little Cayman" longitude="-80.2" municipality="Diggary Point" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" specimenCount="1">
<collectingCountry box="[457,649,866,890]" name="Cayman Islands" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Cayman Islands</collectingCountry>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:4F725324FF9619255585FDBF5C22FAF0:C204B4E9FF96192557D6FCBF5D7AFC90" box="[659,832,866,890]" country="Cayman Islands" longitude="-80.2" municipality="Diggary Point" name="Little Cayman" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Little Cayman</location>
, south coast near 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1038,1204,866,890]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Diggary Point</collectingMunicipality>
, 19°422 N, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1331,1436,866,890]" degrees="80" direction="west" minutes="012" orientation="longitude" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" precision="925" value="-80.2">80°012W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<date box="[192,332,898,922]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" value="1993-11-20">
<collectingDate box="[192,332,898,922]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" value="1993-11-20">20-XI-1993</collectingDate>
</date>
, 
<collectorName box="[345,492,899,922]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">F. J. Burton</collectorName>
, clustered with larvae on severely defoliated 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1276,898,922]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Turneraceae" genus="Turnera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolia">
